no sql vs sql

1. no sql can use horizontal scaling and vertical scaling, while sql typically only use vertical scaling

        horizontal scaling -> increasing the amount of servers then merged them into one database
        vertical scaling -> increasing the power of the existing server (hardware)

2. no sql is schema-less, while sql use strong schema

3. no sql have very little to none relations, while sql have relations 

4. no sql is great in handling huge amount of data reads & writes in small amount of time, while sql isn't 

5. no sql data is nested/merged into one, while sql is distributed in multiple tables (using relations)


